Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Soak your @bamboo skewers{1/2} in cold water (this will prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop @garlic cloves{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it.

Roast the garlic parcel on the baking tray with the chips until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(minced) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Koftas ==

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @chermoula spice mix{1}, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, the remaining garlic and half the lemon zest.

Add the @British beef mince{240%g}, season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Shape into sausage shapes, 2 per person. Flatten to make koftas and thread a skewer through each one.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Transfer the koftas to a large baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Roasted Garlic Yoghurt ==

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a small bowl, combine the roasted garlic and @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Pea Shoot Salad ==

While the koftas bake, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks. Add to a medium bowl with a squeeze of lemon, the @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the dressing and a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

== Lemon Fries ==

When the chips are cooked, crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{30%g} and toss with the remaining lemon zest.

== To Serve ==

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the tomatoes and toss to coat.

Share your chermoula koftas between your plates and drizzle over the roasted garlic yoghurt.

Serve the lemon chips and pea shoot salad alongside. Enjoy!